#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuration Management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:5
msgid ""
"You can use configuration files and channels to manage configuration for "
"your clients, rather than configuring each client manually."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Configuration parameters are scripted and stored in configuration files.  "
"You can write configuration files directly using the {productname} {webui}, "
"or you can upload or link to files that exist in other locations."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Configuration files can be centrally managed, or locally managed.  Centrally "
"managed configuration files are provided by global configuration channels "
"and can be applied to any client subscribed to the {productname} Server.  "
"Locally managed configuration files are used to override centrally managed "
"configuration settings.  They are especially useful for {productname} users "
"who do not have configuration administration privileges, but need to make "
"changes to the clients that they manage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:16
msgid ""
"Configuration channels are used to organise configuration files.  You can "
"subscribe clients to configuration channels, and deploy configuration files "
"as required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Configuration files are version-controlled, so you can add configuration "
"settings, test them on your clients, and roll back to a previous revision as "
"required.  When you have created your configuration channels, you can also "
"perform comparisons between various configuration files, and between "
"revisions of the same configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:23
msgid ""
"Configuration files can be centrally managed, or locally managed.  Centrally "
"managed configuration files are provided by global configuration channels.  "
"Locally managed configuration files are created or uploaded to {productname} "
"directly."
msgstr ""

