#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prepare Traditional Clients for Configuration Management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:78
msgid ""
"Traditional clients require some extra preparation to use configuration "
"management.  If you installed your traditional client with {ay} or "
"{kickstart} you probably already have the appropriate packages.  For other "
"traditional clients, ensure you have installed the relevant tools child "
"channel for your client operating system.  For more information about "
"software channels, see xref:client-configuration:channels.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:80
msgid "The packages you require are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:82
msgid ""
"[path]``mgr-cfg``: base libraries and functions needed by all [path]``mgr-"
"cfg-*`` packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:83
msgid ""
"[path]``mgr-cfg-actions``: required to run configuration actions scheduled "
"via {productname}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:84
msgid ""
"[path]``mgr-cfg-client``: provides a command line interface to the client "
"features of the configuration management system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:85
msgid ""
"[path]``mgr-cfg-management``: provides a command line interface to manage "
"{productname} configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:89
msgid ""
"You can install these packages during the bootstrap process by navigating to "
"menu:Systems[Activation Keys], clicking the activation key you intend to use "
"during bootstrap, and checking the [guimenu]``Configuration File "
"Deployment`` option.  For more information about activation keys, see xref:"
"client-configuration:activation-keys.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

