#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:120
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add Configuration Files, Directories, or Symbolic Links"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:123
msgid ""
"When you have created a configuration channel you can add a configuration "
"file, directory, or symbolic link:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:126
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Adding a Configuration File, Directory, or Symbolic Link"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:128
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Configuration[Channels], and "
"click the name of the configuration channel that you want to add a "
"configuration file to, and navigate to the menu:Add Files[Create File] "
"subtab."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:129
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``File Type`` field, choose whether you want to create a "
"text file, directory, or symbolic link."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:130
msgid ""
"In the [path]``Filename/Path`` field, type the absolute path to the location "
"where the file should be deployed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:131
msgid ""
"If you are creating a symbolic link, type the target file and path in the "
"[guimenu]``Symbolic Link Target Filename/Path`` field."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:132
msgid ""
"Type the [guimenu]``User name`` and [guimenu]``Group name`` for the file in "
"the [guimenu]``Ownership`` field, and the [guimenu]``File Permissions Mode``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:133
msgid ""
"If the client has SELinux enabled, you can configure [guimenu]``SELinux "
"contexts`` to enable the required file attributes (for example: user, role, "
"and file type)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:134
msgid ""
"If the configuration file includes a macro, enter the symbol that marks the "
"beginning and end of the macro."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:135
msgid ""
"Enter the configuration file contents in the [guimenu]``File Contents`` text "
"box, using the script drop-down box to choose the appropriate scripting "
"language."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:136
msgid "Click btn:[Create Configuration File]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "Subscribe Clients to Configuration Channels"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:143
msgid ""
"You can subscribe individual clients to configuration channels by navigating "
"to menu:Systems[System List], selecting the client you want to subscribe, "
"and navigating to the [guimenu]``Configuration`` tab.  To subscribe multiple "
"clients to a configuration channel, you can use the system set manager (SSM)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Subscribing Multiple Clients to Configuration Channels"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:148
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[Systems List] and "
"select the clients you want to work with."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:149
msgid ""
"Navigate to menu:Systems[System Set Manager], and go to the menu:"
"Configuration[Subscribe to Channels] subtab to see the list of available "
"configuration channels."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:150
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: Click the number in the [guimenu]``Systems currently subscribed`` "
"column to see which clients are currently subscribed to the configuration "
"channel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:151
msgid ""
"Check the configuration channels you want to subscribe to, and click btn:"
"[Continue]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:153
msgid ""
"Rank the configuration channels using the up and down arrows.  Where "
"settings conflicts occur between configuration channels, channels closer to "
"the top of the list take precedence."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:157
msgid ""
"Determine how the channels are applied to the selected clients.  Click btn:"
"[Subscribe With Lowest Priority] to add the new channels at a lower priority "
"than currently subscribed channels.  Click btn:[Subscribe with Highest "
"Priority] to add the new channels at a higher priority than currently "
"subscribed channels.  Click btn:[Replace Existing Subscriptions] to remove "
"existing channels and replace them with the new channels."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:158
msgid "Click btn:[Apply Subscriptions]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/configuration-management.adoc:164
msgid ""
"If new configuration channel priorities conflict with existing channels, the "
"duplicate channel is removed and replaced according to the new priority.  If "
"the client's configuration priorities are going to be reordered by an "
"action, the {webui} will require you to confirm the change before proceeding."
msgstr ""

